latestIgtvVideos.title: festival inspired look
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Durga Puja, Durga Pujo, Navratri , whatever you might refer to...the name of the festival itself says a lot about the hype in people’s heart. On this auspicious upcoming festival, I have created a festival inspired makeup look. 

I have tried to give it a Bengali touch by creating decorative motifs and designs.

The “Chondon” (sandalwood) is used not just for style purpose but also its warmth improves circulation and protects from negative energy it is used to unfold Vibrant energy and gives Strength and willpower. 

I have contemprorised the essence of the look. Makeup is not restricted to Women only, even Men can, and men must if they want to. Who is stopping you to be creative? 

So this festive season, do not hesitate to explore your style diva in you.

Products that i used

Good vibes face serum
Lakme face primer
Fit me foundation
NY bae concealer
Sugar cosmetics banana powder
Makeup revolution cranberries and chocolate pallette
Swiss beauty eye shadow pallette
Hilary rhoda eyeshadow pallette
White liquid eyeliner ( brand not mentioned) 
Swiss beauty black eye liner
Lakme iconic mascara
Wet n wild fixing spray
Ny bae lipstick 
Lakme lipstick
Eye lashes and golden glitters.
